          <td style=3D"padding-bottom: 36px; color: #000000; font-size: 16p=
x; line-height: 30px; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0;">On Wednesday mornin=
g, CNN chairman and C.E.O. <b>Mark Thompson </b>kicked off the network=E2=
=80=99s daily 9 a.m. all-hands call with some observations and recommendati=
ons that at least <i>hinted</i> at an editorial strategy for the center-lef=
t news network amid the <b>Trump </b>2.0 era. Throughout the week, CNN had,=
 and <i>has</i>, been dedicating much of its coverage to the torrent of Tru=
mp=E2=80=99s middle-finger cabinet appointments=E2=80=94<b>Matt Gaetz</b> f=
or attorney general; <b>Pete Hegseth </b>for defense secretary; <b>R.F.K. J=
r. </b>for H.H.S. secretary, etcetera. These are the sorts of shock- and re=
vulsion-inducing news developments that have historically driven liberal an=
d anti-Trump audiences to douse their burning scalps in a cooling bath of c=
able news.<br/><br/>But this time around, it seems, Trump=E2=80=99s win and=
 his subsequent staff picks have been so
overwhelmingly dispiriting as to be wholly desensitizing. Audiences for CNN=
 and MSNBC were already declining before the election; since then, they=E2=
=80=99ve fallen off a cliff. The day before CNN=E2=80=99s all-hands, exactl=
y one week <i>after </i>the election, both networks drew some of their smal=
lest audiences on record. In the relevant 25-to-54 demo, each network avera=
ged its lowest total day audience in <i>a quarter of a century</i>, with ju=
st 46,000 for MSNBC and 64,000 for CNN. (Back in the high <b>Zucker</b> day=
s of November 2020, by contrast, CNN registered its highest month <i>ever</=
i>, averaging 560,000<i> in the demo</i> for total day.) Meanwhile, Fox New=
s has thrived, grabbing roughly 75 percent of the cable news audience this =
week, both in total viewers and in the aforementioned under-55 demo. Presum=
ably, <u><a href=3D"https://email.puck.news/e/c/eyJlbWFpbF9pZCI6ImRnVDJ4Z1l=
EQUt2UktxclJLZ0dUTWltdDNvNVVrZV9IQko1eUFLYz0iLCJocmVmIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cucG=
V3cmVzZWFyY2gub3JnL2ludGVybmV0L2ZhY3Qtc2hlZXQvc29jaWFsLW1lZGlhLz90YWJJdGVtP=
TViMzE5YzkwLTczNjMtNDg4MS04ZTZmLWY5ODkyNTY4M2EyZlx1MDAyNnV0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1J=
bitUaGUrUm9vbSstK1NVQlNDUklCRVJTKyUyODExJTJGMTUlMkYyNCUyOVx1MDAyNnV0bV9jb25=
0ZW50PUluK1RoZStSb29tKy0rU1VCU0NSSUJFUlMrJTI4MTElMkYxNSUyRjI0JTI5XHUwMDI2dX=
RtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbF9hY3Rpb25cdTAwMjZ1dG1fc291cmNlPWN1c3RvbWVyLmlvXHUwMDI2d=
XRtX3Rlcm09ZjZjNjA2MTdkYTQyYWJkMTJhIiwiaW50ZXJuYWwiOiJmNmM2MDYxN2RhNDJhYmQx=
MmEiLCJsaW5rX2lkIjoxOTc4ODE4fQ/93f942c6881d6089d9b5b517f79d6150a64a789d4280=
ed639e216a355f4a64a1" style=3D"color:#d40000;text-decoration:none;font-weig=
ht:bold" class=3D"sdf">everyone else</a></u> is busy looking at YouTube, Ti=
kTok, Instagram, and Snapchat, or listening to podcasts, or shoving their h=
ead in the sand.<br/><br/>From Thompson=E2=80=99s perspective, of course, t=
he loss of linear audiences is only the latest urgent catalyst for the futu=
re-facing, digital- and streaming-first strategy he has ostensibly been imp=
lementing since taking over the network more than a year ago. (A strategy w=
hich, as I=E2=80=99ve <u><a href=3D"https://email.puck.news/e/c/eyJlbWFpbF9=
pZCI6ImRnVDJ4Z1lEQUt2UktxclJLZ0dUTWltdDNvNVVrZV9IQko1eUFLYz0iLCJocmVmIjoiaH=
R0cHM6Ly9wdWNrLm5ld3MvbmV3c2xldHRlcl9jb250ZW50L3RoZS1jbm4tcmVja29uaW5nLXdpb=
GxzLWJhY2stdG8td29yay1tYW5kYXRlLWFiY3Mtc2FudHVjY2ktc2Nhcmllcy8_dXRtX2NhbXBh=
aWduPUluK1RoZStSb29tKy0rU1VCU0NSSUJFUlMrJTI4MTElMkYxNSUyRjI0JTI5XHUwMDI2dXR=
tX2NvbnRlbnQ9SW4rVGhlK1Jvb20rLStTVUJTQ1JJQkVSUyslMjgxMSUyRjE1JTJGMjQlMjlcdT=
AwMjZ1dG1fbWVkaXVtPWVtYWlsX2FjdGlvblx1MDAyNnV0bV9zb3VyY2U9Y3VzdG9tZXIuaW9cd=
TAwMjZ1dG1fdGVybT1mNmM2MDYxN2RhNDJhYmQxMmEiLCJpbnRlcm5hbCI6ImY2YzYwNjE3ZGE0=
MmFiZDEyYSIsImxpbmtfaWQiOjE5Nzg4MTl9/75bce11c0a5065704dbf5578cddbd3ead25455=
c9cf8b46302045d6c72c8aea8f" style=3D"color:#d40000;text-decoration:none;fon=
t-weight:bold" class=3D"sdf">reported</a></u>, will necessitate hundreds of=
 layoffs in the weeks ahead.) Honestly, some small part of Thompson may eve=
n <i>welcome </i>the latest Nielsen data, if only because it emphasizes the=
 point he=E2=80=99s been trying to hammer into his charges=E2=80=99 heads, =
gently and then not-so-gently, since he arrived: The future is digital and =
multi-revenue-stream, and it=E2=80=99s time to abandon your nostalgia. <br/=
><br/>In the process of this slow-but-inevitable transformation, Thompson h=
as obviously had to manage the decline of the cable asset, which still pays=
 the bills=E2=80=94a point that the network=E2=80=99s linear natives never =
tire of pointing out. Indeed, Thompson=E2=80=99s appeal, in the eyes of his=
 boss, <b>David Zaslav</b>, wasn=E2=80=99t only that he=E2=80=99d spent a d=
ecade shepherding <i>The New York Times </i>through its own digital
transformation, but also that he had run a global television news network a=
s director general of the BBC in the decade prior to <i>that</i>. And yet, =
the decline of linear, and the diminishing appetite for left-leaning cable =
news, is accelerating more swiftly than either Zaz or Thompson initially ap=
preciated.<br/></td>
